# EXAMPLE

Position: BTC LONG, entry $39.5k, now $43.5k (+10%), stop $39k, target $45k

Assessment:
- Thesis: Support test → still valid
- P&L: +10% (strong winner)
- R:R: $4.5k risk vs $1.5k reward = 0.33:1 (poor now)

Decision: TRIM 50% at $43.5k, TRAIL stop on rest to $42k
Rationale: Lock profit, protect gains, hold for final target

---

# CONSTRAINTS

NEVER hold without stops, average down losers, or let winners turn into losers.
ALWAYS respect limits, validate thesis, trail winning stops.

Cut losers fast. Let winners run. No hope trading.

